If the accident causing injury occurs outside this Commonwealth but within the United States, its territories and possessions, or Canada, the following persons and their survivors suffering loss from injury arising out of maintenance or use of a motor vehicle have a right to basic reparation benefits:
Basic reparation insureds;
The driver and other occupants of a secured vehicle who have not rejected the limitation upon their tort rights, other than:
A vehicle, except for a vehicle as provided in paragraph (c) of this subsection, which is regularly used in the course of the business of transporting persons or property and which is one (1) of five (5) or more vehicles under common ownership; or
A vehicle owned by an obligated government other than this Commonwealth, its political subdivisions, municipal corporations, or public agencies; and
The driver and other occupants of a bus, who have not rejected the limitation upon their tort rights, are Kentucky residents, and boarded a bus in Kentucky, if the bus is:
A secured vehicle;
Registered in Kentucky;
Regularly used in the course of the business of transporting persons or property; and
One (1) of five (5) or more vehicles under common ownership.
